The paper deals with the problem of recovering jointly sparse multichannel vectors from incomplete measurements, which is a problem in signal processing. Therefore, cs.SP (Signal Processing) is a highly likely category. The paper also discusses the role of the rank of the coefficient matrix in determining the difficulty of the recovery problem, which is a topic in linear algebra and numerical analysis. Therefore, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the origins of the sparse approximation problem in array signal processing, which is a subfield of signal processing. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another likely category. The paper also discusses the performance of various algorithms for solving the sparse MMV problem, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category. Finally, the paper also discusses the necessary and sufficient conditions for the uniqueness of the sparse MMV solution, which is a topic in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is another likely category.
